data.current_description: This API replaces user authorized OAuth consent based APIs (Create, Entitle). Issues a timed session token for the given user intent. You can use the session token to redirect the user to Google to finish the signup flow. You can re-generate new session token repeatedly for the same request if necessary, regardless of the previous tokens being expired or not.
data.summary_suggestion: Generate session token for user signup
data.description_suggestion: Generates a time-limited session token that enables partners to redirect users to Google's signup flow for subscription enrollment. This operation replaces the direct OAuth consent flow used by Create and Entitle operations. The returned session token can be used to initiate the user signup process. Session tokens can be regenerated multiple times for the same user intent, even if previous tokens have expired. Returns a session token and its expiration time.
